Day 6  |  June 6, 2025  |  ER Diagram Design

Entity-Relationship Diagram — Entities and Attributes:
The following ER diagram entities were identified and designed for the EventCase Management Suite database:

Entity	Primary Key	Attributes	Relationships
User	user_id (PK)	name, email, password_hash, role, phone, created_at	Creates Events, Books Tickets, Submits Feedback
Event	event_id (PK)	title, description, category, start_date, end_date, venue_id (FK), organizer_id (FK), status, capacity, created_at	Has Venue, Has Sessions, Has Tickets, Has Feedback
Venue	venue_id (PK)	name, address, city, state, pincode, capacity, contact_phone	Hosts many Events
Session	session_id (PK)	event_id (FK), title, start_time, end_time, speaker_name, room	Belongs to Event
Ticket	ticket_id (PK)	event_id (FK), user_id (FK), ticket_type, price, booking_date, status, qr_code	Belongs to User and Event
Payment	payment_id (PK)	ticket_id (FK), amount, payment_date, method, status, transaction_id	Linked to Ticket
Feedback	feedback_id (PK)	event_id (FK), user_id (FK), rating (1-5), comment, submitted_at	Belongs to User and Event
Category	category_id (PK)	name, description, icon	Classifies Events
Notification	notif_id (PK)	user_id (FK), message, type, is_read, created_at	Sent to User

Key Relationships:
•	User (1) ──< Books >── (M) Ticket: One user can book many tickets
•	Event (1) ──< Has >── (M) Ticket: One event can have many tickets booked
•	Event (1) ──< Has >── (M) Session: One event can have multiple sessions
•	Venue (1) ──< Hosts >── (M) Event: One venue can host many events
•	User (1) ──< Submits >── (M) Feedback: One user can give feedback for multiple events
•	Ticket (1) ──< Generates >── (1) Payment: Each ticket booking has one payment record
•	Category (1) ──< Classifies >── (M) Event: One category can have many events
•	User (1) ──< Receives >── (M) Notification: User receives multiple notifications
 
Day 7  |  June 7, 2025  |  Database Schema & Normalization

Normalized Table Definitions (3NF):

users table:
Column	Data Type	Constraint	Description
user_id	INT	PRIMARY KEY, AUTO_INCREMENT	Unique user identifier
